The PSL's Board of Governors is meeting to discuss whether the league will resume behind closed doors or will be indefinitely suspended. Safa has ruled there must be no football activities in the country until further notice. JOHANNESBURG - Premier Soccer League chairperson Irvin Khoza will address the media on Thursday. The PSL Extra-Ordinary Board of Governors met to discuss developments coronavirus pandemic. READ: PSL suspends all mid-week, weekend games On Monday, Khoza announced the PSL will suspend all football fixtures this week until further notice. Meanwhile, the South African Football Association has ruled that there must be no football activities in the country until further notice.